content:
Pretty complex clash, but fairly fun to solve.

I just solved it in Shortest mode and won, but only got 85% because your validators cover an issue that your test cases miss.

Validator 6 is the only one that makes sure that you are careful with minus signs when evaluating the order of operations:
5-9/2+6
-4/2+6
-2+6
4

My code was evaluating based on "[digits][non-digit][digits]", so when it got to the "-2+6" line it evaluated the 2+6 as 8 and then spat out "-8" as the answer. It's a silly mistake, but it would be good to add another test case pair that covers this so that clashers can debug it before submitting if they have the same issue.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Nice work.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: The task to turn the unknown language as given in the default text into some usable collection feels a bit cumbersome, but luckily after that there is still some real coding to do. The 'left to right' is a nice touch to prevent simple eval use.

Your contribution has been uploaded twice. Please remove one of them. The other link is:
https://www.codingame.com/contribute/view/864421f0e2a0ed8e5a58fda5e76b637cb67c9

Input
* Please move "All expressions will be valid, and result in integers." to Constraints section.

* Please move all the explanation to Goal section.

* As the dictionary is always the same, please move it to the Statement part of the stub generator, to simplify input (after that, only one line of input is needed).

The stub generator will also have to be adjusted accordingly.

Output
* As the integer can be any integer, please delete "(positive, negative, or zero)".

Constraints
* Please delete "Expression" and add "in [[F]]".

I will review again after the clash is tidied up as per above comments.

Thanks.
My internet dropped in the middle of submission, so I resubmitted. Thank you for pointing out the duplication. The other has been removed.

Yea. I did not want it to be too trivial, and needed some unique twist instead of just "hey do this simple math". But thanks to 5DN1L's suggestion, I included a copyable dictionary to speed things up.
PS your runebattle.com game is pretty fun, I played it for a while after clashing you about a week or so ago. :)

Thanks. This is my first approved contribution. I will try to get around to adding a leading negative test, nice catch! And thanks again, I put a lot of time into the Alpha version. Have at least one bug to fix, awaiting more feedback. But it is not going anywhere. Big long-term plans, but also starting 2 new jobs rn...
Correction, not 'leading negative test' but rather 'negative first result test'.

If it makes it easier, here's a couple I came up with that would suffice:

gumbro dofta bowfu clebo abido nikta poskul
=> -2
(1-9*2/8)
and
ulpika dofta ribiku nikta abido clebo noflu
=> -8
(3-7/2*4)

Good luck with the new jobs and the game! :)
I will address the other issues as soon as I can.
Okay, I believe I addressed the issues and overall simplified the presentation while keeping all of the important information.

It looks much nicer now!

Goal
* Suggest to add "in the default code" after "a dictionary".

* Please delete "Order of operations is left to right (i.e. 1+2/3 = 1)." in Constraints section, and move it to this section, after "perform the calculation".

Cases
* Please add/revise the TESTS to cover the word "bowfu".

* Please add/revise the VALIDATORS to cover the words "gumbro" and "ulpika".

Thanks.

Done. I added "in the default code" after "a dictionary". I moved order of operations info to GOAL after "perform the calculation". And I replaced some repeat words with the missing words in the TESTS and VALIDATORS and updated the expected results.
Thank you. Looking good now! Just one more comment from me: please change "i.e." to "e.g." in Goal section.
